    "abstractNote": "This paper is a study of certain notions of \u2018Divine Mercy\u2019 in the West Syriac liturgical tradition in the light of Word of God and liturgical prayers. The author tries to explore the theme of \u2018Mercy\u2019 (<i>rahme</i>) in the liturgical prayers in West Syriac liturgical tradition using certain technical phrases coined with the word rahme. Some of the phrases are \u201cDoor of Mercy\u201d (<i>tar\u2019o drahme</i>), \u201cDew of Mercy\u201d (<i>tal\u0101 drahme</i>), \u201cSea of Mercy\u201d (<i>yam\u0101 drahme</i>) and \u201cWings of Mercy\u201d (<i>kenfe drahme</i>).",
